we want to explore the following packets

Offset  Size   Field                         Description
------  ----   ----------------------------  -----------------------------
0       6      Destination MAC               dst_mac
6       6      Source MAC                    src_mac
12      2      EtherType                     0x0800 = IPv4
14      1      Version + IHL                 Version: upper 4 bits (4), IHL: lower 4 bits (Ã—4 bytes)
15      1      DSCP + ECN                    Type of service
16      2      Total Length                  Length of IP packet (header + payload)
18      2      Identification                For fragmentation
20      2      Flags + Fragment Offset       Flags (3 bits) + Fragment offset (13 bits)
22      1      TTL                           Time to live
23      1      Protocol                      6 = TCP, 17 = UDP, etc
24      2      Header checksum               For integrity of the IP header
26      4      Source IP                     src_addr
30      4      Destination IP                dst_addr
34      N      Options (optional)           Present if IHL > 5 (i.e., header > 20 bytes)
34+N    ...    Payload                       e.g., TCP/UDP segment
